Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a railroad sign \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.02,0:00:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that most of us have seen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.82,0:00:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,before we cross a railroad track. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Stop, Look, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.89,0:00:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[and] Listen.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.30,0:00:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And some will say: \N“and Live.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.47,0:00:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why is \Nthis sign there? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.20,0:00:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we know that \Ncrossing a railroad track \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.11,0:00:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,can endanger our lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.88,0:00:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But the danger \Nis not so evident; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not immediately seen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.21,0:00:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be deduced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.35,0:00:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,—you must use \Nyour thinking abilities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.52,0:00:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why \None sign says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.92,0:00:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“See Tracks? Think Train!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.83,0:00:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So we first must stop \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.43,0:00:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then look both ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.23,0:00:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then even engage \Nthe sense of hearing to listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.64,0:00:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we hear a rumble? \Na vibration in the earth? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.74,0:00:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we see a headlight coming our way? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a whistle blowing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, all these indicate a danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.05,0:01:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The train is not in front of us immediately, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.72,0:01:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but we have to be aware \Nof the danger because, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.69,0:01:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as this picture shows, a fast moving train \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.09,0:01:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,just cannot stop immediately \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.66,0:01:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if we happen to be in the middle \Nof the railroad tracks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.63,0:01:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were there, \Nwe definitely would be killed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.27,0:01:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To avoid such a tragedy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.54,0:01:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we therefore must use what the Bible calls \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.11,0:01:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,our “perceptive powers” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.54,0:01:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern the danger that is before us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.55,0:01:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we must take appropriate action \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.02,0:01:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to find safety to make sure \Nthat we are not victimized by the danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.66,0:01:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this well illustrates \Nwhat Jehovah has been telling us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,through his Word \Nand through his organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is telling us today to stop, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.93,0:02:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,look, and listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.44,0:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Look around you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.44,0:02:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Discern the times that we’re living in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.84,0:02:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re living in the last days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.31,0:02:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The end is very near. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.38,0:02:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The great tribulation is about to take place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.38,0:02:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s necessary to have discernment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to come to this conclusion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.99,0:02:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said you would need discernment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.09,0:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At Luke 17:20, 21, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.25,0:02:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,he says that the Kingdom \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.40,0:02:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,would not be “coming \Nwith striking observableness.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.10,0:02:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It would take discernment \Nto understand the signs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and what it would mean \Nand what action to take. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This ability to discern requires cultivation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.55,0:02:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,—we need to work on it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.55,0:02:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible at Hebrews 5:14 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.42,0:02:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,calls it the “powers of discernment” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.52,0:02:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or what we used to call \Nthe “perceptive powers.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.16,0:03:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we learned in yesterday’s text \Nwhen it referred to the prophet Daniel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.10,0:03:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,he was exemplary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.17,0:03:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in using his perceptive powers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to perceive, or to discern, the will of God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.07,0:03:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was necessary for him to do so \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.54,0:03:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to avoid the dangerous situation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.25,0:03:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that he and his companions were in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.85,0:03:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there at the palace in Babylon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Daniel continued to cultivate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.89,0:03:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,these powers of discernment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.56,0:03:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Later on in his life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.76,0:03:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he made a deep study of the prophecies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,especially those of Jeremiah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.80,0:03:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he concluded, or discerned, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.10,0:03:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,where they were in the stream of time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.10,0:03:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,—that the end \Nof the 70-year desolation of Jerusalem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,was coming to its conclusion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And this moved him to take \Nspecific action to prepare himself \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as other faithful Jews \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.25,0:03:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they could proceed \Nwith Jehovah’s will and purpose. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.12,0:04:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He therefore understood the times \Nand events that were taking place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.29,0:04:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the deep study that he did, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.73,0:04:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was able to discern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what was taking place \Nin the world around him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jesus taught us to do \Nsomething very similar. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.27,0:04:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He told us to cultivate discernment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.67,0:04:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and he used \Na beautiful illustration to do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.44,0:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Open your Bibles, please, \Nto the book of Luke, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll look at chapter 21 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.45,0:04:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and verses 29-31. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.72,0:04:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And here Jesus uses this technique \Nof “stop, look, listen, and live.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.02,0:04:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He says in verse 29: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Notice the fig tree \Nand all the other trees.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So stop and look around you, he says. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.77,0:04:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And verse 30, it says: \N“[And] when they are budding.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.44,0:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, look at these plants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.54,0:04:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and “you see it for yourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.94,0:04:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and know that now the summer is near.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So discern it; \Nperceive what is taking place here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.88,0:05:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he tells us and listen in verse 31: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“Likewise also you, \Nwhen you see these things happening, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.35,0:05:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,know that the Kingdom of God is near.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.22,0:05:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So here Jesus was telling us \Nto stop, look, listen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.73,0:05:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we would live.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, “the faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.87,0:05:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—they’re guided by the head \Nof the congregation, Jesus Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.94,0:05:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And he is providing direction \Nto us in a very similar way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.51,0:05:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to help us sharpen \Nour powers of discernment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.71,0:05:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to comprehend and understand \Nwhat’s going on around us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.95,0:05:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s through the pages of The Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.62,0:05:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and our assemblies and conventions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.02,0:05:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are told to stop\N—leave off your everyday life and concerns \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and stop for a moment; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.80,0:05:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then look into God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—read it and see what the Bible has to say \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.84,0:05:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jehovah’s will and purpose \Nand especially our time period; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.74,0:06:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and then take time to listen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.88,0:06:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to the explanations provided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.45,0:06:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,through “the faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.72,0:06:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about prophecies and about our time period \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.75,0:06:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nearness of the great tribulation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, today, we are receiving \Na very clear message \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.83,0:06:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah God’s organization \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.03,0:06:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,through Jesus Christ \Nand through “the faithful and discreet slave” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.13,0:06:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that the great tribulation is imminent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.87,0:06:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how should this information affect us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.31,0:06:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one thing, the anxieties of life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—the things that immediately confront us \Non a day-to-day basis—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.98,0:06:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,can sap our energy \Nand can totally distract us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.65,0:06:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,away from the bigger issues. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.19,0:06:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus warned us against this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.46,0:06:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, going back to the book \Nof Luke chapter 17, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.83,0:06:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there Jesus uses the accounts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of Noah as well as Sodom and Gomorrah \Nto be a warning to us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:07:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There He says that the days of the Son of man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,would be like the days of Noah and Sodom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.37,0:07:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And why? \NBecause people would be distracted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.54,0:07:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with the mundane cares of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.88,0:07:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s these mundane cares of life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.52,0:07:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that can truly dull our powers of perception. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We would not be able to discern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.92,0:07:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where we are in the stream of time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or the danger that is confronting us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to really be careful \Nthat we don’t allow these things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to dull our powers of discernment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.07,0:07:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we can find ourselves \Njust wandering onto a railroad track \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.67,0:07:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and not really looking, \Nnot listening, being distracted, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.88,0:07:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and before you know it, \Na train could overtake us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s exactly what is happening \Nto people in the world today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.78,0:07:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re distracted by these things, \Nand they’re failing to take notice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.69,0:07:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah God is coming \Nat them at full speed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.82,0:07:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to execute judgment \Nagainst Satan’s wicked world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.79,0:08:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when we sharpen \Nour powers of discernment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we clearly see the signs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.30,0:08:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus said that you would. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.30,0:08:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He said at Luke 17:24 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.70,0:08:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that it would be like lightning flashing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.24,0:08:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from one end of the sky \Nto the other end of the sky. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But it would be only \Nbecause our powers of discernment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.78,0:08:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,would see these things and understand them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we see very clearly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.45,0:08:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We look around at the political world today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.45,0:08:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can see \Nthese “lightning flashes” all around us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In Daniel’s vision of chapter 2 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.03,0:08:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—the iron and the clay \Nof the final world power— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.86,0:08:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we see how fragmented they are, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.87,0:08:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,how weak and ineffectual \Nthis world government is. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At 2 Timothy 3:1-5, the attitudes of people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,including those who are leaders in the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.41,0:08:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are arrogant and blasphemous and haughty. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.48,0:08:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,These are clear indications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.78,0:08:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are very near the time of the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.52,0:08:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, these individuals \Nand these governments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:09:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are very much like \Nan illustration that we saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.29,0:09:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in the October 15, 1971, \Nissue of The Watchtower \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of a little ant standing on a railroad track, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and here we see \NGod’s Kingdom coming at them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.17,0:09:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And we, obviously, \Nsee what the outcome will be. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They will be completely pulverized \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by the power and speed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.84,0:09:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s executional forces.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see, therefore, it’s important \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.58,0:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to sharpen our powers of discernment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,—to cultivate this quality—\Nso that we are not caught off guard, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.66,0:09:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we always see the danger, \Nand we can take appropriate action. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.73,0:09:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So every day, let us stop, look, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.86,0:09:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and listen to Jehovah’s warnings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.27,0:09:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help us stay out \Nof the danger zone, \N
